<blockquote>
<p>Today, very few teenagers work full time jobs, and the number of teens employed in summer jobs has decreased from ~60% in 1994, to ~40% in 2008.[29][29]: Camarota S, Jensenius, K. : <a href="http://www.cis.org/articles/2010/teen-study.pdf">‚ÄúA Drought of Summer Jobs: Immigration and the Long-Term Decline in Employment Among U.S.-Born Teenagers‚Äù</a>. In: Backgrounder. Center for Immigration Studies; 2010. <a href="http://chronopause.com/index.php/2011/08/20/interventive-gerontology-1-0-02-first-try-to-make-it-to-the-mean-diet-as-a-life-extending-tool-part-3/">http://chronopause.com/index.php/2011/08/20/interventive-gerontology-1-0-02-first-try-to-make-it-to-the-mean-diet-as-a-life-extending-tool-part-3/</a></p>
